---
import Section from './Section.astro'
---

<Section id="bet">
  <h2 class="max-w-3xl text-balance font-sans text-3xl font-medium lowercase leading-snug text-lp-fg md:text-4xl">
    when you run many agents on one codebase, the model isn't the bottleneck — the shared state is.
  </h2>

  <!-- to-scale wall-clock bar: worker.run fills 99.9%; the platform sliver is
       nearly invisible on purpose. the magnifier zooms the sliver — wow from
       honest proportions, not styling. -->
  <figure class="mt-12">
    <!-- no role="img" here: it would flatten the subtree for assistive tech
         and swallow the interactive zoom button inside. the bar's visible
         text + the figcaption already state every number. -->
    <div id="wallclock-bar" class="relative h-10 overflow-hidden rounded border border-lp-border bg-lp-surface-2">
      <div class="flex h-full items-center px-4 font-mono text-xs text-lp-muted">worker.run · 99.9% of wall-clock</div>
      <div class="absolute inset-y-0 right-0 w-[2px] bg-lp-accent" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <button
        id="sliver-btn"
        type="button"
        class="absolute inset-y-0 right-0 hidden w-11 cursor-zoom-in"
        aria-expanded="false"
        aria-controls="sliver-zoom"
        aria-label="zoom the platform sliver"></button>
    </div>

    <div id="sliver-zoom" hidden class="mt-2 overflow-hidden rounded border border-lp-border bg-lp-surface">
      <div class="border-b border-lp-border px-4 py-1.5 font-mono text-[11px] text-lp-muted">
        the sliver, magnified ~2000× — this is the whole platform
      </div>
      <div class="flex h-10 items-center justify-between px-4 font-mono text-xs">
        <span class="text-lp-accent">oracle.claim · 2.4ms mean</span>
        <span class="text-lp-muted">the platform adds ~0.05% of wall-clock</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <figcaption class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-2 font-mono text-xs text-lp-muted">
      <span>drawn to actual scale — the sliver on the right is the entire platform</span>
      <span class="text-lp-fg">oracle.claim · <b>2.4ms</b> mean · the platform adds ~0.05%</span>
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p class="mt-10 max-w-2xl text-pretty text-lp-muted">
    so the win doesn't come from which model is typing — it comes from what the agents share.
    auralis makes that shared state explicit: every agent reaches the same brain and gets the same
    answer, whether it's in another process, on another machine, or running tomorrow.
  </p>
</Section>

<script>
  // magnifier: hover or tap/Enter the sliver's 44px hit area to zoom it.
  // click is the single toggle — focus deliberately does NOT auto-open,
  // otherwise the first Enter after tabbing in would immediately close it.
  // decoration-time only — the zoom panel toggles, nothing animates a number.
  const btn = document.getElementById('sliver-btn') as HTMLButtonElement | null
  const zoom = document.getElementById('sliver-zoom')
  if (btn && zoom) {
    btn.classList.remove('hidden')
    const set = (open: boolean) => {
      zoom.hidden = !open
      btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(open))
    }
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => set(zoom.hidden))
    btn.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => set(true))
    btn.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => { if (document.activeElement !== btn) set(false) })
  }
</script>
